Table of Contents

Data Explaination¶

  • Opendata (Case Western Reserve University Bearing Data Center, Stationary conditions)
    • The rolling bearing experimental setup
      • Experiment picture
      • Schematic illustration
    • The faults are seeded on the drive-end bearings
      • Normal, inner fault, outer fault, ball fault
    • Accelerometers are attached to the drive end of the motor housing and the sampling frequency is 12kHz.

3. Feature Extraction + DL¶

3.1 Rotor Data Feature Extraction¶

In [27]:
# feature extract
def extfeat(x):
    fvector = []
    
    # time domain feature
    peak = np.max(np.abs(x),1)
    fvector.append(peak)
    
    rms = np.sqrt(np.mean(x**2,1))
    fvector.append(rms)
    
    kurtosis = scipy.stats.kurtosis(x,1)
    fvector.append(kurtosis)
    
    skewness = scipy.stats.skew(x,1)
    fvector.append(skewness)
    
    smr = (np.sum(np.sqrt(np.abs(x)),1)/len(x))**2
    fvector.append(smr)
    
    pp = np.max(x,1) - np.min(x,1)
    fvector.append(pp)
    
    kurtosis_factor = fvector[1]/rms**4
    fvector.append(kurtosis_factor)
    
    impulse_factor = fvector[0]/(np.sum(np.abs(x),1)/len(x))
    fvector.append(impulse_factor)
    
    margin_factor = np.max(x,1)/fvector[7]
    fvector.append(margin_factor)
    
    crest_factor = fvector[0]/fvector[1]
    fvector.append(crest_factor)
    
    shape_factor = fvector[1]/(np.sum(np.abs(x),1)/len(x))
    fvector.append(shape_factor)
    
    # frequency domain feature
    s = np.abs(np.fft.fft(x,axis=1))
    k = np.arange(1,len(s[0])+1)[np.newaxis]
    
    spec_cent = np.sum(k*s,1)/np.sum(s,1)
    fvector.append(spec_cent)
    
    rmsf = np.sqrt(np.mean(s**2,1))
    fvector.append(rmsf)
    
    root_vari_f = np.sqrt(np.mean((s-np.mean(s,1)[:,np.newaxis])**2,1))
    fvector.append(root_vari_f)
    
    fvector = np.array(fvector)
    
    return fvector.T

feature_name = ['Peak', 'RMS', 'Kurtosis', 'Skewness', 'Square mean root', 'Pk-pk', 'Kurtosis factor', \
                'Impulse factor', 'Margin factor', 'Crest factor', 'Shape factor',  \
                'Spectral centroid', 'RMS of frequency', 'Root variance of frequency']

def get_FFT(x):
    
    n = x.shape[-1]
    x_fft = np.fft.fft(x, axis = -1)/n
    x_fft = x_fft[..., range(int(n/2))]
    x_fft = np.abs(x_fft)
    
    return x_fft
In [43]:
N = 2**8
theta = np.linspace(0, 4*np.pi, N)
x = np.zeros(theta.shape)

for n in range(1, 20, 2):
    x = x + 4/(np.pi*n)*np.sin(n*theta)

Fs = 2**10
T = 1/Fs

N = 2*Fs

t = np.arange(0,N)*T

k = np.arange(0,N)
f = (Fs/N)*k

x1 = np.cos(2*np.pi*50*t)
x2 = np.cos(2*np.pi*100*t)

x = np.zeros(t.shape)
x[0:int(N/2)] = x1[0:int(N/2)]
x[int(N/2):-1] = x2[int(N/2):-1]

z = 1/2*(x1 + x2)

# Show STFT of first data for each class  
# Use fs = 12000
#     windowsize = 110

data = [normal, inner, outer, ball]

Fs = 12000 # Sampling rate
windowsize = 110
window = np.hanning(windowsize)
nfft = windowsize
noverlap = windowsize/2

plt.figure(figsize = (12, 12))

for i in range(4):
    f, t, Sxx = spectrogram(data[i][0], 
                            Fs, 
                            window = window, 
                            noverlap = noverlap, 
                            nfft = nfft, 
                            scaling = 'spectrum', 
                            mode = 'psd')

    plt.subplot(2,2,i+1)
    plt.pcolormesh(t, f, Sxx)
    plt.title('Classes : {}'.format(classes[i]), fontsize = 15)
    plt.ylabel('Frequency [Hz]', fontsize = 12)
    plt.xlabel('Time [sec]', fontsize = 12)
plt.show()

# Preprocessing 
# Transform time domain data to STFT image for all data

train_data_STFT = []
test_data_STFT = []

for i in range(len(train_x)):
    _, _, Sxx = spectrogram(train_x[i],
                            Fs,
                            window = window,
                            noverlap = noverlap,
                            nfft = nfft,
                            scaling = 'spectrum',
                            mode = 'psd')
    train_data_STFT.append(Sxx)
    
for i in range(len(test_x)):
    _, _, Sxx = spectrogram(test_x[i],
                            Fs,
                            window = window,
                            noverlap = noverlap,
                            nfft = nfft,
                            scaling = 'spectrum',
                            mode = 'psd')
    test_data_STFT.append(Sxx)
    
train_data_STFT = np.array(train_data_STFT)
test_data_STFT = np.array(test_data_STFT)

3.3.1 STFT + CNN¶

# Define model

cnn_network = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
    tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(32,
                           (3,3),
                           activation = 'relu',
                           padding = 'SAME',
                           input_shape = (56, 56, 1)
                          ),
    tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D((2,2)),
    
    tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(64,
                           (3,3),
                           activation = 'relu',
                           padding = 'SAME'),
    tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D((2,2)),
    
    tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(64,
                           (3,3),
                           activation = 'relu',
                           padding = 'SAME'),
    tf.keras.layers.MaxPool2D((2,2)),
    
    tf.keras.layers.GlobalAveragePooling2D(),
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(4, activation = 'softmax')
])

cnn_network.summary()
